defs.docs: # Type-based Serialization and Deserialization

defs.name: InvalidMarkerRead
defs.docs:
The enclosed I/O error occured while trying to read a MessagePack
 marker.

defs.name: InvalidDataRead
defs.docs:
The enclosed I/O error occured while trying to read the encoded
 MessagePack data.

defs.name: TypeMismatch
defs.docs: A mismatch occured between the decoded and expected value types.

defs.name: OutOfRange
defs.docs: A numeric cast failed due to an out-of-range error.

defs.name: LengthMismatch
defs.docs: A decoded array did not have the enclosed expected length.

defs.name: Uncategorized
defs.docs:
An otherwise uncategorized error occured. See the enclosed `String` for
 details.

defs.name: Syntax
defs.docs:
A general error occured while deserializing the expected type. See the
 enclosed `String` for details.

defs.name: Utf8Error
defs.docs: An encoded string could not be parsed as UTF-8.

defs.name: DepthLimitExceeded
defs.docs: The depth limit was exceeded; not currently used.

defs.name: Error
defs.value: Error::{InvalidMarkerRead, InvalidDataRead, TypeMismatch, OutOfRange, LengthMismatch, Uncategorized, Syntax, Utf8Error, DepthLimitExceeded}
defs.docs: Enum representing errors that can occur while decoding MessagePack data.

defs.name: write
defs.value: fn <W, T> (wr: &mut W, val: &T) -> Result<(), Error>
defs.docs:
Serialize the given data structure as MessagePack into the I/O stream.
 This fyunction uses compact representation - structures as arrays

defs.name: write_named
defs.value: fn <W, T> (wr: &mut W, val: &T) -> Result<(), Error>
defs.docs:
Serialize the given data structure as MessagePack into the I/O stream.
 This function serializes structures as maps

defs.name: to_vec
defs.docs:
Serialize the given data structure as a MessagePack byte vector.
 This method uses compact representation, structs are serialized as arrays

defs.name: to_vec_named
defs.docs:
Serializes data structure into byte vector as a map
 Resulting MessagePack message will contain field names

defs.name: Raw
defs.docs:
Helper that allows both to encode and decode strings no matter whether they contain valid or
 invalid UTF-8.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Constructs a new `Raw` from the UTF-8 string.

defs.name: from_utf8
defs.docs: Converts a vector of bytes to a `Raw`.

defs.name: is_str
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the raw is valid UTF-8.

defs.name: is_err
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the raw contains invalid UTF-8 sequence.

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs: Returns the string reference if the raw is valid UTF-8, or else `None`.

defs.name: as_err
defs.docs:
Returns the underlying `Utf8Error` if the raw contains invalid UTF-8 sequence, or
 else `None`.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: Returns a byte slice of this raw's contents.

defs.name: into_str
defs.docs: Consumes this object, yielding the string if the raw is valid UTF-8, or else `None`.

defs.name: into_bytes
defs.docs: Converts a `Raw` into a byte vector.

defs.name: is_str

defs.name: is_err
defs.docs: Returns `true` if the raw contains invalid UTF-8 sequence.

defs.name: as_str
defs.docs: Returns the string reference if the raw is valid UTF-8, or else `None`.

defs.name: as_err
defs.docs:
Returns the underlying `Utf8Error` if the raw contains invalid UTF-8 sequence, or
 else `None`.
